{"word":"σπαράσσω","slug":"σπαράσσω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σπαράσσω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>akin to <a href='S:σπαίρω'><el>σπαίρω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to tear, rend in pieces, mangle</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>lacerare</el>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <el>σπαράσσεσθαι κόμας</el> <i>to tear one's</i> hair, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to rend asunder</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to pull to pieces, attack</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>conviciis lacerare</el>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}